It snowed a lot.

4
00:00:13,820 --> 00:00:15,220
Okay.

5
00:00:16,390 --> 00:00:18,460
- Hello. - Okay.

6
00:00:18,860 --> 00:00:20,060
Today...

7
00:00:20,060 --> 00:00:21,460
- Okay! - Kim Jong Kook!

8
00:00:21,460 --> 00:00:24,230
Hey, it isn't cold today!

9
00:00:24,230 --> 00:00:26,660
- Kim Jong Kook! - It's not so cold.

10
00:00:27,070 --> 00:00:28,870
Why are you shy? Why?

11
00:00:28,870 --> 00:00:31,300
- What? - Why are you shy?

12
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:34,640
Jong Kook, why are you...

13
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:37,710
It's natural that a celebrity is dressed like this. Why are you shy?

14
00:00:37,710 --> 00:00:40,280
- I just... - Jong Kook, what's with you?

15
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:42,880
- What's going on? - We're having new writers today,

16
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:43,950
- Hello. - so are you welcoming them?

17
00:00:43,950 --> 00:00:46,850
We have new writers here today.

18
00:00:46,850 --> 00:00:49,150
I went to meet our production staff...

19
00:00:49,150 --> 00:00:51,690
- on my YouTube channel before. - You did?

20
00:00:51,690 --> 00:00:53,590
They told me to dress up for the opening.

21
00:00:53,860 --> 00:00:55,690
- Right. They said that. - I watched it.

22
00:00:55,690 --> 00:00:57,100
I watched it.

23
00:00:57,660 --> 00:00:59,560
- Right. - I saw that.

24
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:02,400
- So, as I put this on today, - Yes.

25
00:01:02,670 --> 00:01:04,070
- I had this thought. - What did you think?

26
00:01:04,070 --> 00:01:06,040
Instead of wasting my energy on this...

27
00:01:07,070 --> 00:01:08,470
Does it make you waste your energy?

28
00:01:09,610 --> 00:01:11,980
You're just wearing clothes. What's the big deal?

29
00:01:11,980 --> 00:01:13,410
You're a celebrity.

30
00:01:13,410 --> 00:01:15,350
- What about this? - I'd rather save my energy...

31
00:01:15,350 --> 00:01:16,680
Why does it require your energy?

32
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:18,880
And I'll work harder during the shoot.

33
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:20,890
- Hey. - I understand...

34
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:22,620
how Steve Jobs and Mark Zuckerberg feel.

35
00:01:22,620 --> 00:01:23,620
That they always wear the same outfit?

36
00:01:23,620 --> 00:01:25,790
- They always wear the same thing. - I see.

37
00:01:25,790 --> 00:01:28,390
- This makes you waste your energy? - You're a celebrity.

38
00:01:28,390 --> 00:01:30,960
- I know, but... - Ji Seon seemed pleased today.

39
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:32,730
She was wearing a Celine beanie.

40
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:34,600
- Right. - She was so happy.

41
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,970
- She wears many designer products. - Right.

42
00:01:36,970 --> 00:01:39,240
As his stylist, Ji Seon... What?

43
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:41,570
I just said something quietly here.

44
00:01:41,570 --> 00:01:43,980
I said, "Seok Jin's hair looks good today." And he heard it.

45
00:01:43,980 --> 00:01:45,710
"Hey, say it out loud."

46
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:46,910
- I see. - "Louder."

47
00:01:47,580 --> 00:01:50,720
- Seok Jin's hair looks good today. - Ji Seon looked so happy today.

48
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:53,420
- Say it out loud. - Ji Seon was so pleased...

49
00:01:53,690 --> 00:01:55,220
- Today... - I love your hair today.

50
00:01:55,220 --> 00:01:57,190
- Your hair looks great. - Now...

51
00:01:57,190 --> 00:01:58,960
- You look like the Little Prince. - Did I do well?

52
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:01,290
Give me 50 dollars. You should give me some allowance.

53
00:02:01,290 --> 00:02:02,590
- I'll buy you tteokbokki. - He will buy me tteokbokki.

54
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:04,700
- He will buy tteokbokki. - He changed his hairstylist.

55
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:05,960
Really?

56
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:07,500
It's 20 dollars cheaper.

57
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:10,670
That's not true. You... The previous hairstylist...

58
00:02:10,670 --> 00:02:11,940
The previous hairstylist...

59
00:02:11,940 --> 00:02:13,470
He said "Hair shovel."

60
00:02:13,470 --> 00:02:14,710
- They used a shovel. - She might get the wrong idea.

61
00:02:14,710 --> 00:02:16,310
- That's not true. - I feel bad for the hairstylist.

62
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:18,240
- He moved to a cheaper salon. - No.

63
00:02:18,510 --> 00:02:20,040
That's only natural.

64
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:21,880
- You should find a cheaper place. - Right.

65
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:23,180
The previous hairstylist was good,

66
00:02:23,180 --> 00:02:25,420
- Of course. - but he found a cheaper place.

67
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:26,720
- That's not true. - You should save money.

68
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:29,220
Your hair looks great anyway. It's a lot better.

69
00:02:29,220 --> 00:02:30,960
You do look like the Little Prince from behind.

70
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:33,660
That's right. What's with you?

71
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:35,260
- He's pleased. - He gave you a thumbs-up.

72
00:02:35,260 --> 00:02:37,130
That doesn't happen a lot in the morning.

73
00:02:37,130 --> 00:02:40,270
Actually, my youthful appearance has been on the rise.

74
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:41,270
- Who? You? - Me.

75
00:02:41,270 --> 00:02:42,300
I hear that a lot.

76
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:44,470
- That's true. - Hair is important for men.

77
00:02:44,470 --> 00:02:45,870
- I know, right? - Yes.

78
00:02:45,870 --> 00:02:47,310
I think you did something about your eyes.

79
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:48,310
- Where? - What did you do with your eyes?

80
00:02:48,310 --> 00:02:49,570
- I think you did something. - Really?

81
00:02:49,570 --> 00:02:50,780
- Seok Jin! - I swear.

82
00:02:50,780 --> 00:02:51,780
- You didn't? - What do you want me to swear to?

83
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:53,510
Your eyes are swollen.

84
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:55,510
See? Because you look young...

85
00:02:55,510 --> 00:02:57,320
- Hey. - Seok Jin, you should...

86
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:59,850
pluck out the white hair here. I'm serious. Look.

87
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:01,590
- Look. You have to pull it out. - It's really there.

88
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:02,820
Is it white hair?

89
00:03:02,820 --> 00:03:03,820
It's really there.

90
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,720
- You have to pull it out. - Is it white hair?

91
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,460
- Seok Jin. - Pull it out in secret.

92
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:09,930
- Seok Sam is... - That's called Udambara.

93
00:03:10,330 --> 00:03:11,460
- Look. I pulled it out. - Did you get it?

94
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:13,570
- It's white hair. - That's true.

95
00:03:13,570 --> 00:03:16,030
- Don't do that. - We have to take an insert shot.

96
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,570
- That's true. - I dropped it.

97
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:18,670
- It brings him good luck. - Hey.

98
00:03:18,670 --> 00:03:21,370
- It's Udambara. Don't pull it out. - It's just hair.

99
00:03:21,370 --> 00:03:22,570
- It's longevity hair. - I sometimes get it.

100
00:03:22,570 --> 00:03:24,210
Longevity hair grows here.

101
00:03:24,210 --> 00:03:25,880
Gosh, Seok Jin.

102
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:29,180
All right. We have guests for today.

103
00:03:29,180 --> 00:03:31,250
- Really? - We will bring in the guests.

104
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:32,980
- Oh, dear. - Roy Kim.

105
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:35,090
- Hey. - It's been a long time.

106
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:36,120
This is amazing.

107
00:03:36,490 --> 00:03:38,060
Hello. Nice to meet you.

108
00:03:38,790 --> 00:03:40,860
- Hello. - You're here after a long time.

109
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:42,560
- It's been ten years. - Ten years?

110
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:45,060
- He comes here once a year. - Right. Once a year.

111
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:46,430
He comes every winter.

112
00:03:46,430 --> 00:03:48,570
- And he always feels cold. - Right.

113
00:03:48,570 --> 00:03:49,830
I feel like crying.

114
00:03:49,830 --> 00:03:53,000
- He's a weakling. - Be careful.

115
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,610
You look a little tired.

116
00:03:57,610 --> 00:03:59,680
- I'm so tired. - You do look tired.

117
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:02,450
- He's even good at this. - He's such a weakling.

118
00:04:12,090 --> 00:04:15,130
Salute. I'm Kim Sang Woo, a reserve sergent from the 1,259th batch.

119
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:16,660
- Someone's shouting over there. - Which batch are you from?

120
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:17,700
He asks which batch I'm from.

121
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:20,100
Which batch are you from, Kim Sang Woo?

122
00:04:20,570 --> 00:04:22,330
Which Marine batch are you from?

123
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:25,170
Salute. I'm from the 1,259th batch.

124
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:27,240
Hey.

125
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:29,210
Hasn't it been a long time since the last time you came here?

126
00:04:29,210 --> 00:04:30,310
- It's been ten years. - Ten years?

127
00:04:30,310 --> 00:04:31,840
- I know. - Kyu Hyun.

128
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:34,480
This is your first time here. No, it's not his first time.

129
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,310
- Hello. - He comes here...

130
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:38,180
- like twice a year. - Hello.

131
00:04:38,450 --> 00:04:40,720
- Twice a year. Come here. - Hi.

132
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:43,050
We have Roy Kim...

133
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:45,190
and Kyu Hyun here today.

134
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:46,860
I'm a guest who always comes around this time of year.

135
00:04:46,860 --> 00:04:48,660
Right. You come when it's cold.

136
00:04:48,660 --> 00:04:50,030
- That's true. - A winter man.

137
00:04:50,030 --> 00:04:52,500
- He comes when it's cold. - I think he comes in every winter.

138
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,600
Our show has no one to ask about your Marine batch.

139
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,870
What a relief.

140
00:04:55,870 --> 00:04:57,200
- Why? - He served in the Marine Corps.

141
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,300
He was a marine? Awesome.

142
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:59,970
We might have a marine among the production staff.

143
00:04:59,970 --> 00:05:02,210
Kyu Hyun's manager already...

144
00:05:02,210 --> 00:05:04,040
- He asked you that? - Yes.

145
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,810
He served in the Marine Corps before I did.

146
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:07,680
So it feels like it hasn't been a long time since his discharge.

147
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:09,050
- Has it been a year? - It's been five years.

148
00:05:09,050 --> 00:05:10,420
- Five years? - He says "Already."

149
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:12,280
- Already? - It's been five years, but still...

150
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:13,890
I've been hearing the question for five years.

151
00:05:13,890 --> 00:05:15,620
- Has it been five years? - Yes.

152
00:05:15,620 --> 00:05:16,890
- It feels like it's been a year. - That was a long time ago.

153
00:05:16,890 --> 00:05:18,960
- I thought it was last year. - I know.

154
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:21,490
- It's been a long time. - Ye Eun.

155
00:05:21,490 --> 00:05:22,960
You're peeking at him through the crowd.

156
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:24,800
- That's not true. - From a distance.

157
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:26,330
- No. - Who are you peeking at?

158
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:28,170
- Who is it? Kyu Hyun or Roy? - Who were you looking at?

159
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:29,430
- Kyu Hyun or Roy? - Who were you peeking at?

160
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:31,140
- That can't be me. - What are you talking about?

161
00:05:31,140 --> 00:05:32,270
- No? - Of course, it's him.

162
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:34,140
- Is it Roy Kim? - No. I wasn't looking.

163
00:05:34,140 --> 00:05:36,870
The thing is, Ye Eun likes marines.

164
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:38,180
No.

165
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,950
She likes marines among all the soldiers.

166
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:42,880
- No. - The ghost-catching marines.

167
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:46,720
By the way, Kyu Hyun knows himself very well.

168
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,890
- Sure. - He says it's not him.

169
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:49,490
He said, "That can't be me."

170
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,160
- No. - I've been here a few times,

171
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:53,060
- and she's not interested in me. - That's not true.

172
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:54,530
- It's not like that. - Not Gwanghawmun.

173
00:05:54,530 --> 00:05:56,160
- No. - Not at all.

174
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:59,360
Roy, you say you're back here after ten years.

175
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:02,830
But when I came here ten years ago,

176
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:04,300
I couldn't exactly say I was a guest.

177
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:05,400
- Which episode was it? - What did you do?

178
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,940
- For a short time? - Back then, my wish...

179
00:06:07,940 --> 00:06:10,140
was to appear on Running Man as a guest.

180
00:06:10,140 --> 00:06:12,210
- And I got a call from this show. - Okay.

181
00:06:12,210 --> 00:06:14,480
- I was really excited to come here. - And?

182
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:16,350
And there were 100 celebrities here.

183
00:06:16,350 --> 00:06:18,780
- I see. It was 100 versus 100. - Were you there?

184
00:06:18,780 --> 00:06:20,720
This is 100 versus 100!

185
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:24,090
It's time for the mission!

186
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:27,630
You have to hold out!

187
00:06:27,630 --> 00:06:29,430
- I see. It was 100 versus 100. - Were you there?

188
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:30,960
Who called you back then?

189
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,430
- I don't even remember. - Who called him?

190
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:34,670
- Who was it? - Seok Jin called him.

191
00:06:34,670 --> 00:06:36,330
- It was Seok Jin. - I see.

192
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,500
You're unbelievable.

193
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,270
- What's wrong with you? - Seriously, what's with you?

194
00:06:39,270 --> 00:06:40,510
How did we know each other?

195
00:06:40,510 --> 00:06:42,870
I have no idea.

196
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:44,880
- I just found that out today. - You and I...

197
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:47,150
- You went to his agency. - Right.

198
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:49,450
- I guess that's how it happened. - That's it.

199
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:50,520
I don't have your phone number.

200
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:52,680
- And I don't have yours. - You don't?

201
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:53,680
- No. - We have a deep connection.

202
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,250
- I thought we first met today. - We can become close now.

203
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:56,350
Of course.

204
00:06:56,350 --> 00:06:57,860
So, we can say this is your first time here.

205
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:59,060
- It's my first guest appearance. - Right.

206
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,220
I see.

207
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,460
It's his first time here as our main guest.

208
00:07:01,460 --> 00:07:03,460
- Back then... - It's really touching...

209
00:07:03,460 --> 00:07:06,330
because Roy is here when he has nothing to promote.

210
00:07:06,330 --> 00:07:07,470
- Really? - Yes.

211
00:07:07,470 --> 00:07:10,030
I came here to say that I've grown a lot over the past ten years.

212
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:11,870
- Really? - I'm finally on Running Man.

213
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:13,670
- You're finally here. - Now, I'm the main guest.

214
00:07:13,670 --> 00:07:15,670
- You've grown a lot. - Yes.

215
00:07:15,670 --> 00:07:18,180
- You can be here now. - He's grown a lot.

216
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:20,880
Kyu Hyun, what's new?

217
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:22,680
- Is your new song coming out? - I bet something's coming out.

218
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:25,050
- I have news. - What? Your song is coming out?

219
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:26,080
- Last year... - Kyu Hyun wouldn't come here...

220
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,420
- without a new song. - Right.

221
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:29,190
- He has a definite reason. - Right.

222
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:31,090
- He's thorough about that. - Am I thorough?

223
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:32,360
Last year, I came here with "The Man Who Laughs."

224
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,590
That's right.

225
00:07:33,590 --> 00:07:35,360
- Yes. This year... - Is it "The Man Who Cries?"

226
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:37,700
No. It's "Death Note" this time.

227
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,530
- Right. - I want to watch it.

228
00:07:40,530 --> 00:07:41,630
Let's watch it together.

229
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:43,430
Are you L?

230
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:44,770
I play Light.

231
00:07:44,770 --> 00:07:46,070
- Light. - He plays Light.

232
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:47,070
Is it the main character?

233
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:49,840
Are you going to sing a number from the musical for us?

234
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,480
- Of course. - I knew it.

235
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,840
You should sing one for us.

236
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:54,380
- Sing for us. - That's nice.

237
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:57,680
But can I give you an excuse before I sing?

238
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,850
- Yes. - Your throat?

239
00:07:58,850 --> 00:08:00,690
I finished my concert yesterday.

240
00:08:00,690 --> 00:08:03,150
- You have a sore throat? - I returned on a night flight.

241
00:08:03,490 --> 00:08:04,860
I slept for only three hours before coming here.

242
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:07,590
Singers always make excuses like that.

243
00:08:07,590 --> 00:08:09,130
- Right. - Am I right?

244
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:11,130
- They never feel good. - I have a cold.

245
00:08:11,130 --> 00:08:12,860
- I'm aching all over my body. - Body aches,

246
00:08:12,860 --> 00:08:15,300
- busy schedule, - Tonsillitis.

247
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:16,400
- or tonsillitis. - I knew it.

248
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:19,040
I'm always worried about singing live on Running Man.

249
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,040
- It's 10am now. - That's right.

250
00:08:21,070 --> 00:08:23,940
- You have all the bad conditions. - Right.

251
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:26,440
- Let's do it karaoke style. - Okay.

252
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:28,050
