00:47:26,550 --> 00:47:29,480
Is it that hard to treat your friend of 30 years to a meal?

1277
00:47:30,090 --> 00:47:32,390
It's not like you can spend R coins anywhere else.

1278
00:47:33,360 --> 00:47:34,890
- Hold on. - Come on.

1279
00:47:34,890 --> 00:47:36,330
They're just plastic coins...

1280
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:38,630
with stickers on them.

1281
00:47:38,630 --> 00:47:40,930
Here, that's my life and my whole world.

1282
00:47:40,930 --> 00:47:42,900
No money, no food. No money, no meals.

1283
00:47:42,900 --> 00:47:44,270
Do you badly want to be treated to a meal by your junior?

1284
00:47:44,730 --> 00:47:46,600
- We're in big trouble. - This is bad.

1285
00:47:46,970 --> 00:47:48,370
I'm all out of coins.

1286
00:47:49,200 --> 00:47:50,510
I'm getting the penalty today.

1287
00:47:50,710 --> 00:47:52,440
Same here. I don't think I can escape it.

1288
00:47:52,440 --> 00:47:53,680
Then let's spend everything we have.

1289
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:55,780
I don't have any coins to spend.

1290
00:47:56,250 --> 00:47:58,080
- How many do you have? - I have 50R.

1291
00:47:58,210 --> 00:47:59,410
You don't have enough either.

1292
00:47:59,750 --> 00:48:01,680
- How much do you have? - I...

1293
00:48:01,680 --> 00:48:04,590
I have 150R, so we can at least eat a meal.

1294
00:48:09,960 --> 00:48:11,090
I'm a crow with 100R.

1295
00:48:11,430 --> 00:48:13,630
- Do you have 150R? - She has 150R?

1296
00:48:13,730 --> 00:48:16,200
I'll spend what I have so that we can eat.

1297
00:48:16,600 --> 00:48:17,630
Right.

1298
00:48:17,870 --> 00:48:19,400
Together, you only have 200R.

1299
00:48:19,900 --> 00:48:20,900
Right.

1300
00:48:20,900 --> 00:48:22,200
Are you sure you only have 50R?

1301
00:48:22,440 --> 00:48:23,470
Of course.

1302
00:48:23,770 --> 00:48:24,940
I'm not lying.

1303
00:48:25,610 --> 00:48:27,580
Why are you doubting me when you're completely broke?

1304
00:48:28,180 --> 00:48:29,440
Haha, come on.

1305
00:48:30,310 --> 00:48:31,310
I...

1306
00:48:31,310 --> 00:48:33,720
I almost forgot I was talking to "the" Yang Se Chan.

1307
00:48:33,720 --> 00:48:35,780
- Stop that. - I...

1308
00:48:35,780 --> 00:48:37,720
He's "the" Yang Se Chan.

1309
00:48:37,720 --> 00:48:38,850
- Of course. - Don't.

1310
00:48:38,850 --> 00:48:40,160
Hear me out.

1311
00:48:40,720 --> 00:48:43,130
But he's completely broke!

1312
00:48:43,130 --> 00:48:44,460
Haha, please.

1313
00:48:45,060 --> 00:48:47,600
Help a brother out, Haha.

1314
00:48:48,060 --> 00:48:49,160
We'll see.

1315
00:48:49,530 --> 00:48:50,630
Haha, just this once.

1316
00:48:51,670 --> 00:48:53,340
I'll see how you treat me today.

1317
00:48:53,900 --> 00:48:55,670
- There's nothing I can do. - Se Chan.

1318
00:48:55,670 --> 00:48:57,470
- Yes? - I'm the one paying...

1319
00:48:57,470 --> 00:48:59,210
for both your meals.

1320
00:49:00,110 --> 00:49:01,910
- I can pay some of it. - He'll pay some of it.

1321
00:49:01,910 --> 00:49:03,610
- Okay. - I can pay some of it.

1322
00:49:03,610 --> 00:49:04,980
Pay up first, then.

1323
00:49:04,980 --> 00:49:06,110
You need to give her 50R.

1324
00:49:06,110 --> 00:49:08,350
Once we get there and decide what to eat,

1325
00:49:08,350 --> 00:49:10,890
- I'll pay up after we order. - Give it to her right now.

1326
00:49:10,890 --> 00:49:11,950
- No way. - Give it to me now.

1327
00:49:11,950 --> 00:49:13,420
Don't be like that.

1328
00:49:13,420 --> 00:49:14,560
How about this?

1329
00:49:14,720 --> 00:49:16,360
Let's say I give you 50R.

1330
00:49:16,560 --> 00:49:19,060
I can pay that much. If I do, don't let him eat with us.

1331
00:49:19,700 --> 00:49:20,930
Don't be so petty over food.

1332
00:49:20,930 --> 00:49:22,360
You're ridiculously petty.

1333
00:49:23,470 --> 00:49:25,130
- Ridiculously? - You're ridiculously petty.

1334
00:49:25,130 --> 00:49:27,970
- Hold on. - All this over a meal...

1335
00:49:27,970 --> 00:49:30,070
- for one of your juniors? - Was I wrong to suggest that?

1336
00:49:30,070 --> 00:49:32,870
- Why can't you... - He's trying to freeload.

1337
00:49:32,870 --> 00:49:34,910
- But... - I'll give you 50R,

1338
00:49:34,910 --> 00:49:37,250
so don't give him any food.

1339
00:49:37,310 --> 00:49:39,650
- But you still won't pay up. - I'll give it to you right now.

1340
00:49:41,150 --> 00:49:42,620
Food at the market is always delicious.

1341
00:49:42,620 --> 00:49:44,550
Gyeongdong Market is huge.

1342
00:49:44,550 --> 00:49:46,520
This is what you come to a market to enjoy.

1343
00:49:46,520 --> 00:49:48,290
Goodness, that looks good.

1344
00:49:48,820 --> 00:49:49,960
That looks so good.

1345
00:49:51,360 --> 00:49:52,960
This is exactly why I love traditional markets.

1346
00:49:52,960 --> 00:49:54,260
That looks good.

1347
00:49:54,260 --> 00:49:55,760
You know market tteokbokki tastes the best.

1348
00:49:55,760 --> 00:49:57,670
- Of course. - Let's find a good place to eat.

1349
00:49:57,670 --> 00:49:59,230
This is incredible.

1350
00:49:59,230 --> 00:50:00,570
Just get going for now.

1351
00:50:01,040 --> 00:50:02,540
- Hold on. - Jokbal?

1352
00:50:02,540 --> 00:50:03,640
- Check this out. - This place looks good.

1353
00:50:03,640 --> 00:50:05,110
They serve gukbap.

1354
00:50:05,110 --> 00:50:06,110
That looks good.

1355
00:50:06,110 --> 00:50:07,740
That looks really good, doesn't it?

1356
00:50:07,740 --> 00:50:10,080
- There's jokbal. - Gamjatang.

1357
00:50:10,350 --> 00:50:11,880
- And budaejjigae. - Budaejjigae.

1358
00:50:11,880 --> 00:50:13,350
There's also jjageuli.

1359
00:50:13,350 --> 00:50:15,780
Manila clam kalguksu is served...

1360
00:50:15,780 --> 00:50:17,390
- in a large bowl. - The portions are huge.

1361
00:50:17,390 --> 00:50:18,790
Right? So rather than something we cook at the table...

1362
00:50:18,790 --> 00:50:20,260
- Manila clam kalguksu? - The servings are huge.

1363
00:50:20,260 --> 00:50:21,560
Manila clam kalguksu?

1364
00:50:21,590 --> 00:50:22,860
Manila clam kalguksu?

1365
00:50:22,960 --> 00:50:24,830
How about we check out the jokbal place first?

1366
00:50:24,830 --> 00:50:26,660
- Don't forget, it was my idea. - Sure.

1367
00:50:27,760 --> 00:50:29,260
- Haha. - I'm surrounded now.

1368
00:50:29,260 --> 00:50:30,870
- That tone makes you sound... - Yes?

1369
00:50:30,870 --> 00:50:32,500
like a eunuch. Stop it.

1370
00:50:32,500 --> 00:50:34,900
With a voice this deep? Not a chance.

1371
00:50:35,200 --> 00:50:37,010
You need to get 50R from him.

1372
00:50:37,010 --> 00:50:38,410
That's the only way you'll spend just 100R.

1373
00:50:39,040 --> 00:50:40,910
- By the way, Seok Sam. - Yes?

1374
00:50:41,010 --> 00:50:42,510
- Seok Jin. - You're not eating today.

1375
00:50:42,510 --> 00:50:44,350
I can't believe you only have five coins.

1376
00:50:44,350 --> 00:50:45,510
Your sack's pretty heavy.

1377
00:50:45,580 --> 00:50:46,580
- What? - Hold on.

1378
00:50:46,580 --> 00:50:47,920
- There's no way... - I have other things in here.

1379
00:50:47,920 --> 00:50:50,090
- Yes, I have two phones in here. - Really?

1380
00:50:50,090 --> 00:50:51,820
That's not it. It just doesn't make sense.

1381
00:50:51,820 --> 00:50:53,320
- It's really heavy. - You're treating that...

1382
00:50:53,320 --> 00:50:55,490
- like it's precious. - What can I say when I'm broke?

1383
00:50:55,490 --> 00:50:57,660
Darn. As the oldest,

1384
00:50:57,660 --> 00:50:59,230
- it feels nice... - Scoot over to us.

1385
00:50:59,230 --> 00:51:00,530
- to have a bag... - Then...

1386
00:51:00,530 --> 00:51:01,960
- full of coins. - Right.

1387
00:51:01,960 --> 00:51:04,070
What if you end up having more than I do?

1388
00:51:04,070 --> 00:51:05,330
- No way. - Kyu Hyun.

1389
00:51:05,330 --> 00:51:06,540
- Not me. - That's not true.

1390
00:51:06,540 --> 00:51:09,240
I don't think they gave a lot to the crows. I mean, magpies.

1391
00:51:09,240 --> 00:51:10,310
So...

1392
00:51:10,370 --> 00:51:13,540
My surname is Cho, so it's Cho Magpie.

1393
00:51:14,440 --> 00:51:16,180
Anyway...

1394
00:51:16,850 --> 00:51:17,980
It says 300.

1395
00:51:18,050 --> 00:51:19,750
- All right, 20 percent. - Two.

1396
00:51:19,750 --> 00:51:20,750
How come you have so much?

1397
00:51:20,750 --> 00:51:23,220
- We saw how much you have. - Everyone saw.

1398
00:51:23,790 --> 00:51:25,290
- Can I borrow some? - You never know.

1399
00:51:25,290 --> 00:51:26,690
I was surprised when I picked up Seok Jin's bag.

1400
00:51:26,690 --> 00:51:27,820
- Because it was heavy? - Yes.

1401
00:51:28,320 --> 00:51:29,620
And it's like I said.

1402
00:51:29,620 --> 00:51:32,130
After we finish filming,

1403
00:51:32,130 --> 00:51:33,660
these coins are useless.

1404
00:51:33,700 --> 00:51:35,630
But right now, they're our whole world.

1405
00:51:35,630 --> 00:51:36,970
How are they our whole world?

1406
00:51:36,970 --> 00:51:38,530
I mean,

1407
00:51:38,630 --> 00:51:40,370
our friendship is forever.

1408
00:51:40,470 --> 00:51:41,470
What?

1409
00:51:41,770 --> 00:51:43,710
- Right? - What's forever?

1410
00:51:43,710 --> 00:51:44,870
- I mean... - Fine. I get it for now.

1411
00:51:44,870 --> 00:51:46,640
Just decide what we're having.

1412
00:51:46,640 --> 00:51:49,010
You're paying, so let's have whatever you want.

1413
00:51:49,140 --> 00:51:50,450
Sure.

1414
00:51:51,150 --> 00:51:53,620
Doesn't bossam usually come in big portions?

1415
00:51:53,620 --> 00:51:55,550
You're right. We can order a large dish.

1416
00:51:56,850 --> 00:51:58,550
- Doesn't that sound great? - It does.

1417
00:51:59,050 --> 00:52:01,160
Haven't you had bossam recently?

1418
00:52:01,290 --> 00:52:03,790
- What? - I actually had some yesterday.

1419
00:52:04,960 --> 00:52:07,630
You don't get a say in this.

1420
00:52:07,630 --> 00:52:09,930
I don't, but you can take that into account.

1421
00:52:09,930 --> 00:52:10,930
Why should I?

1422
00:52:10,930 --> 00:52:12,500
- Out of all these options, - You...

1423
00:52:12,500 --> 00:52:13,640
do you have to get the same dish...

1424
00:52:13,640 --> 00:52:15,140
- I had yesterday? - Just shut it.

1425
00:52:15,140 --> 00:52:16,870
- Up there. - Why don't we go up there?

1426
00:52:16,870 --> 00:52:19,040
- Let's go up there. - There's a food court.

1427
00:52:19,170 --> 00:52:20,380
- Here we go. - There are restaurants here.

1428
00:52:20,380 --> 00:52:21,540
Just don't pick bossam.

1429
00:52:21,540 --> 00:52:23,310
You can have anything else you want.

1430
00:52:23,310 --> 00:52:26,380
It's too bad we can only share a dish.

1431
00:52:27,150 --> 00:52:29,550
- I really want jjajangmyeon. - That sounds great.

1432
00:52:29,550 --> 00:52:31,550
- I'd love some jjajangmyeon. - We talked about that earlier.

1433
00:52:31,550 --> 00:52:33,050
- Doesn't that sound great? - It does.

1434
00:52:33,150 --> 00:52:35,390
I'd love some jjajangmyeon. Do they have it here?

1435
00:52:35,390 --> 00:52:37,130
I had jjajangmyeon yesterday.

1436
00:52:37,130 --> 00:52:38,490
- What? - You didn't!

1437
00:52:38,490 --> 00:52:39,530
I had jjajangmyeon for lunch.

1438
00:52:39,530 --> 00:52:40,660
- Really? - For lunch?

1439
00:52:40,660 --> 00:52:41,660
- For real. - Is that for real?

1440
00:52:41,660 --> 00:52:43,700
Why are you... You don't have a say in this.

1441
00:52:43,700 --> 00:52:44,730
I know.

1442
00:52:44,730 --> 00:52:45,730
Why are you trying to decide what we eat?

1443
00:52:45,730 --> 00:52:46,940
It's jjajangmyeon and bossam.

1444
00:52:46,940 --> 00:52:48,970
- I'm choosing what I want. - Fine.

1445
00:52:48,970 --> 00:52:50,140
Have what you want.

1446
00:52:50,140 --> 00:52:51,770
There are a lot of delicious places here.

1447
00:52:53,210 --> 00:52:55,280
- They even have rice pots. - How about rice pots?

1448
00:52:56,180 --> 00:52:57,750
Rice pots? I...

1449
00:52:57,980 --> 00:52:59,150
Rice pots...

1450
00:52:59,510 --> 00:53:00,650
I had some three days ago.

1451
00:53:00,650 --> 00:53:03,020
You said I could pick,

1452
00:53:03,020 --> 00:53:04,190
so why are you rejecting everything?

1453
00:53:04,190 --> 00:53:05,920
You eat a wide variety of foods.

1454
00:53:06,420 --> 00:53:08,820
- I do. - You're getting on my nerves.

1455
00:53:08,820 --> 00:53:09,960
Where to?

1456
00:53:10,330 --> 00:53:11,860
- I wouldn't mind... - Seok Jin.

1457
00:53:11,860 --> 00:53:12,860
some spicy pollack stew.

1458
00:53:12,860 --> 00:53:14,360
Pick whatever you want.

1459
00:53:14,600 --> 00:53:15,860
- Why you... - But...

1460
00:53:15,860 --> 00:53:17,470
- You say that but... - Didn't you already reject...

1461
00:53:17,470 --> 00:53:18,500
- two of his suggestions? - I suggested two dishes,

1462
00:53:18,500 --> 00:53:20,500
- but you rejected them both. - Hi!

1463
00:53:20,500 --> 00:53:21,540
Hello.

1464
00:53:21,540 --> 00:53:23,470
Happy Lunar New Year.

1465
00:53:23,710 --> 00:53:24,710
- Goodness. - Hello.

1466
00:53:25,040 --> 00:53:26,170
- He's handsome. - Everything I say...

1467
00:53:26,510 --> 00:53:28,410
Did you hear her say that I'm handsome?

1468
00:53:28,410 --> 00:53:29,540
- Hello! - She's only joking.

1469
00:53:29,540 --> 00:53:31,550
- Yes, hello. - Goodness.

1470
00:53:31,550 --> 00:53:33,350
- Hi. - This is Yu Jae Seok.

1471
00:53:33,350 --> 00:53:35,080
- Goodness. - Hello.

1472
00:53:35,250 --> 00:53:37,090
Hello, ma'am.

1473
00:53:39,350 --> 00:53:41,660
- It's really you. - Hello.

1474
00:53:42,360 --> 00:53:45,030
Hello.

1475
00:53:45,190 --> 00:53:46,430
Jae Seok.

1476
00:53:46,860 --> 00:53:48,200
Hello.

1477
00:53:48,660 --> 00:53:49,860
Hey, stir-fried octopus.

1478
00:53:50,470 --> 00:53:51,500
Stir-fried octopus?

1479
00:53:52,530 --> 00:53:54,600
- Pollack stew. - Pollack stew sounds good.

1480
00:53:54,600 --> 00:53:55,700
Rice and soup.

1481
00:53:55,870 --> 00:53:57,970
- How about rice and soup? - Hello.

1482
00:53:58,140 --> 00:53:59,340
- I can have whatever I want. - I like it.

1483
00:53:59,340 --> 00:54:00,910
- How about rice and soup? - Sounds great.

1484
00:54:00,910 --> 00:54:02,440
- Is that okay? - Rice and soup?

1485
00:54:02,440 --> 00:54:04,210
- Let's check it out. - Let's take a look.

1486
00:54:04,210 --> 00:54:05,610
- Rice and soup... - That's a great option.

1487
00:54:05,610 --> 00:54:06,620
- Rice and soup is great. - Rice and soup and...

1488
00:54:06,620 --> 00:54:08,450
- Hot soup and... - We can order one each.

1489
00:54:08,950 --> 00:54:10,350
- Hello. - Hello.

1490
00:54:10,650 --> 00:54:12,150
What do you serve with rice and soup?

1491
00:54:12,250 --> 00:54:14,320
- With all that? - No way.

1492
00:54:14,320 --> 00:54:15,660
That looks good. Is this it?

1493
00:54:15,660 --> 00:54:17,260
- That looks delicious. - This is great.

1494
00:54:17,260 --> 00:54:18,830
- I love it. - Can we have some right away?

1495
00:54:18,830 --> 00:54:20,530
- Of course. - We don't have to wait.

1496
00:54:20,530 --> 00:54:22,200
- Where should we go? - For how many people?

1497
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:23,230
- Three. - Three.

1498
00:54:23,230 --> 00:54:25,530
- This way, then. - Thank you.

1499
00:54:25,700 --> 00:54:27,740
- He's leading the way. - I didn't expect this.

1500
00:54:27,740 --> 00:54:29,370
- Hello. - Hello. Here we go.

1501
00:54:29,370 --> 00:54:31,440
- Hi. - Hello, ma'am.

1502
00:54:31,440 --> 00:54:32,610
Goodness, it's Yu Jae Seok.

1503
00:54:32,610 --> 00:54:33,640
Hello.

1504
00:54:33,640 --> 00:54:35,240
- Once they leave... - We can sit here.

1505
00:54:35,240 --> 00:54:37,080
Here? I didn't think they'd have a system like this.

1506
00:54:37,080 --> 00:54:38,450
- I see. - We can eat here.

1507
00:54:38,450 --> 00:54:39,910
- Let's sit here. - Sure thing.

1508
00:54:40,520 --> 00:54:42,380
- I'll sit here. - I'm broke,

1509
00:54:42,380 --> 00:54:43,890
so I should do...

1510
00:54:43,890 --> 00:54:45,750
as the others say.

1511
00:54:45,750 --> 00:54:48,320
Just pay for your meal.

1512
00:54:48,320 --> 00:54:50,790
I've been saying I'm broke this whole time.

1513
00:54:50,790 --> 00:54:53,030
I don't believe you at all.

1514
00:54:53,190 --> 00:54:54,930
- I mean... - I'll watch the show later on.

1515
00:54:54,930 --> 00:54:56,260
It's the truth.

1516
00:54:56,260 --> 00:54:57,670
- I'm broke. - I'll absolutely curse you.

1517
00:54:57,670 --> 00:54:59,970
If I had enough coins, I'd pay 50R.

1518
00:54:59,970 --> 00:55:01,870
- You know me. - Don't have the fish.

1519
00:55:01,870 --> 00:55:03,040
Sure thing.

1520
00:55:04,410 --> 00:55:05,970
- Now... - What can I do?

1521
00:55:05,970 --> 00:55:07,980
I'll pay for Jae Seok's,

1522
00:55:07,980 --> 00:55:09,340
so just pay five coins

1523
00:55:09,340 --> 00:55:11,350
I'll pay for Jae Seok's, so just pay 50R.

1524
00:55:11,350 --> 00:55:13,180
- That's great. - Jae Seok's meal...

1525
00:55:13,180 --> 00:55:14,280
Thank you so much.

1526
00:55:14,280 --> 00:55:16,180
Don't you forget this.

1527
00:55:16,180 --> 00:55:18,290
If the time comes for you to choose...

1528
00:55:18,290 --> 00:55:19,420
